claim.claim-text:
1. A process for producing a food product comprising: 
A) providing a dry mix; 
B) combining the dry mix with a liquid to form a slurry; 
C) preparing the slurry; 
D) adding a first additive to the prepared slurry to form a first ingredient; 
E) adding a second additive to the prepared slurry and forming a second ingredient; 
F) adding a third additive to the dry mix to form a third ingredient; 
G) preparing the third ingredient; 
H) flowing the first ingredient and the third ingredient in side-by-side intersecting streams to form a first multi-layer product; 
I) causing the first multi-layer product to flow in an output direction; and 
J) causing the second ingredient to flow in the output direction at two locations adjacent to the first direction; 
K) combining the flowing multi-layer product with the flowing second ingredient at the two locations to form a final multi-layer product.

10. A product formed by the steps of: 
providing a dry mix; 
A) combining the dry mix with a liquid to form a slurry; 
B) preparing the slurry; 
C) adding a first additive to the prepared slurry to form a first ingredient; 
D) adding a second additive to the prepared slurry and forming a second ingredient; 
E) adding a third additive to the dry mix to form a third ingredient; 
F) preparing the third ingredient; 
G) flowing the first ingredient and the third ingredient in side-by-side intersecting streams to form a first multi-layer product; 
H) flowing the first ingredient and the third ingredient in side-by-side intersecting streams to form a first multi-layer product; 
I) causing the first multi-layer product to flow in an output direction; and 
J) causing the second ingredient to flow in the output direction at two locations adjacent to the first direction; 
K) combining the flowing multi-layer product with the flowing second ingredient at the two locations to form a final multi-layer product.

16. A forming die for forming a multi-layer food product comprising: 
A) a body; 
B) a first flow path defined through said body; 
C) a second flow path defined through said body to be side-by-side with said first flow path, said second flow path contacting said first flow path at a first location; 
D) a third flow path defined through said body to be on two sides of said first and second flow paths to sandwich said first and second flow paths between said third flow path; and 
E) said third flow path being separated from said first and second flow paths for a predetermined length of said first and second flow paths and contacting said first and second flow paths at a second location that is spaced from the first location.

20. A system for forming a food product comprising: 
A) a supply of dry mix material; 
B) a pump; 
C) a supply of liquid; 
D) a first preparation unit fluidically connected to said supply of dry mix material and to said supply of liquid, a first ingredient being formed in said first preparation unit; 
E) a second preparation unit, a second ingredient being formed in said second preparation unit; 
F) a supply of first additive; 
G) a die fluidically connected to said first preparation unit and fluidically connected to said second preparation unit and to said supply of first additive in a manner such that said first additive is added to the first ingredient before the first ingredient reaches said die; 
H) a supply of second additive; 
I) a third preparation unit fluidically connected to said supply of second additive, a third ingredient being formed in said third preparation unit; 
J) said third preparation unit being fluidically connected to said die; and 
K) said die including a first flow path for said first ingredient, a second flow path for said second ingredient, a third flow path for said third ingredient, said first and third flow paths being sandwiched by said second flow path.

